<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddc399d00-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s1750f"><num value="1750f">§ 1750f.</num><heading> Rules and regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary is authorized and directed to make such rules and regulations as may be necessary to carry out the provisions of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddc399d01-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/act/1934-06-27/ch847">June 27, 1934, ch. 847</ref>, title IX, § 907, as added <ref href="/us/act/1951-09-01/ch378">Sept. 1, 1951, ch. 378</ref>, title II, § 201, <ref href="/us/stat/65/301">65 Stat. 301</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/90/19/s1/a/3">Pub. L. 90–19, § 1(a)(3)</ref>, <date date="1967-05-25">May 25, 1967</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/81/17">81 Stat. 17</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
